1 (2) the spouse, adult child, parent or guardian, adult sibling, or adult
2 grandchild of the deceased person.
3 (h) Rules. Pursuant to 3 V.S.A. chapter 25, the Department shall adopt
4 rules as necessary for the purposes of implementing, administering, or
5 enforcing the correction or amendment of death certificates pursuant to
6 subsection (g) of this section. The rules adopted pursuant to this subsection
7 shall include:
8 (1) a list of the documents that may be accepted as prima facie evidence
9 of the deceased person’s gender identity, including any relevant information
10 contained in an advanced directive;
11 (2) the forms and affidavits that shall be used to attest to the deceased
12 person’s identity at the time of death; and
13 (3) procedures for an individual to file a predesignation of their gender
14 identity, which may be used by the State Registrar to render a final decision
15 concerning the correction or amendment of a death certificate.
16 Sec. 2. DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH; RULEMAKING; LEGISLATIVE
17 INTENT
18 It is the intent of the General Assembly that the Department of Health,
19 exercising rulemaking authority pursuant to this act, shall adopt a
20 comprehensive procedure for a health care professional or surviving family
21 member to attest to the gender identity of a deceased person. The procedure
